reviewText: This series is a lot of fun and you get to see a lot of old stars and favorites of the genre which is a great tip of the hat to this folks that entertained us all those years ago.  There was plenty of action in the story, lotsa pretty ladies and seeing Reba McEntire in the black leather outfit was worth the price of the dvd.  There was the usual drama of the poker games, the various chases and back and forth stealing and recovery of the cash stake for the big game in San Francisco as well as the historical figures and western heroes that have made this stuff interesting and pleasing for so long.  It looked like the cast had a lot of fun making the movie and I had a lot of fun watching.  Thanx Kenny, Reba, Claude, Hugh, Mickey, Chuck, Johnny, Gene, Clint, James, Linda, Doug, Brian,Dub, David, Patrick, Jack and Paul.  Also thanx to all the "new" folks that helped make this such an enjoyable, fun dvd.
summary: Reba in black leather is worth the price of the dvd . . .
